<br>
Yes, 2 handers generate less aggro than 2 weapons, still here are some posible scenarios to use them:<br>
<br>
-You dont want the aggro, because you are not the MT today.<br>
-You hold aggro with spells, instead of damage.<br>
-You want to cast between swings, without losing a single hit. Will need a high delay for this.<br>
-You cant dual wield (knights) and want to go for damage today.<br>
-You are hitting a mob with huge AC (Luclin) and most of your hits are for minimal damage, still your damage bonus will be added to every swing so a 'slow' 2 hander will do more damage and hold better aggro.<br>
-You are tanking a mob that ripostes for 500 too often, and you can hold his aggro with taunt/spells. The less times you hit him, the better.<br>
<br>
